						               													<description>New Horizons is the advanced version of the original Colonial Space Wars, a strategic 2-D wargame based on a sci-fi universe.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;During the game, 1 inch square pieces move across a rectangular board divided into squares arranged in rows and columns. Each player has a number of units in his army, which is set depending on the faction they are playing. We call this combination of units a &amp;ldquo;Combat Sword&amp;quot;. Four factions are available for players:  Union of Terra, Centauri Brotherhood, Heimdall Industries and Ascaryan Infestation.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Game pieces represent the units of troops and vehicles in each army. Pieces have two sides, &amp;quot;Front&amp;quot; (Illustration and Health marker) and &amp;quot;Back&amp;quot; (Name, Attributes and Skills). Some units grant X &amp;quot;Command Points&amp;quot; at the beginning of each player turn, and all units require a number of &amp;quot;Command Points&amp;quot; to be used that turn (which is known as &amp;ldquo;Activating &amp;rdquo; the unit). When all command points are spent, the opponent&amp;rsquo;s turn begins. Each unit, upon being activated, can move and act in any order. The possible actions are &amp;ldquo;Move&amp;rdquo;, &amp;ldquo;Embark/disembark&amp;rdquo;, &amp;ldquo;Attack&amp;rdquo; and &amp;ldquo;Use active skills&amp;rdquo;.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A typical game is a Sudden Death match, where the winner is the player that eliminates their opponent&amp;rsquo;s ability to activate units. However, in addition to this a description of advanced rules and missions for more experienced players is given.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
